cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.SI. 

The problem involves allocation of regions in a unit square, which is a classic computational geometry problem. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves optimization and analysis of algorithms, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of space-filling curves suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
